- The two look alike.

716
00:24:07,005 --> 00:24:09,535
- No.
- I'm reminded of Jang Hoon.

717
00:24:09,675 --> 00:24:11,434
That's when Jang Hoon is lying face down.

718
00:24:11,435 --> 00:24:13,274
Isn't that Jang Hoon's first birthday?

719
00:24:13,275 --> 00:24:14,705
- First birthday photo?
- First birthday photo.

720
00:24:15,045 --> 00:24:17,044
- Both of you look like it.
- I see Jang Hoon in the dog.

721
00:24:17,045 --> 00:24:19,944
If a big dog with such features shows up,

722
00:24:19,945 --> 00:24:21,014
It's all you.

723
00:24:21,015 --> 00:24:22,444
most of them look almost identical to me.

724
00:24:22,445 --> 00:24:23,754
- It's because...
- A big dog in the countryside...

725
00:24:23,755 --> 00:24:25,054
is Jang Hoon.

726
00:24:25,055 --> 00:24:26,454
- Exactly.
- Right?

727
00:24:26,455 --> 00:24:28,284
It's not the face that looks like SHUHUA.

728
00:24:28,285 --> 00:24:30,994
- The white fur.
- Yes, it's the white fur.

729
00:24:30,995 --> 00:24:32,555
- It looks like SHUHUA.
- SHUHUA,

730
00:24:32,625 --> 00:24:33,894
did you never bask in...

731
00:24:33,895 --> 00:24:35,224
Have you never photosynthesized in your life?

732
00:24:35,225 --> 00:24:36,595
Your skin is really pale.

733
00:24:37,395 --> 00:24:38,795
It's UV rays!

734
00:24:39,365 --> 00:24:41,835
- People might misunderstand.
- Photosynthesis.

735
00:24:42,065 --> 00:24:43,704
- That's photosynthesis.
- It's photosynthesis.

736
00:24:43,705 --> 00:24:45,905
- That's photosynthesis.
- He's right.

737
00:24:46,445 --> 00:24:49,105
Ho Dong said photosynthesis because he didn't know about UV rays.

738
00:24:49,375 --> 00:24:51,144
Photosynthesis is his nickname.

739
00:24:51,145 --> 00:24:52,315
(In scarlet letters)

740
00:24:52,575 --> 00:24:53,714
I don't like the sunlight.

741
00:24:53,715 --> 00:24:55,645
- You don't?
- I hate the sunlight.

742
00:24:56,245 --> 00:24:58,085
But you need a certain amount of sunlight every day.

743
00:24:58,285 --> 00:24:59,884
That's why my vitamin D...

744
00:24:59,885 --> 00:25:02,085
- Vitamin D?
- levels are really low.

745
00:25:02,355 --> 00:25:03,394
Supplements.

746
00:25:03,395 --> 00:25:05,624
- Are you taking vitamin D?
- I am.

747
00:25:05,625 --> 00:25:07,324
Were you always that pale?

748
00:25:07,325 --> 00:25:08,864
- Yes.
- She's always been pale.

749
00:25:08,865 --> 00:25:09,934
Interesting.

750
00:25:09,935 --> 00:25:12,034
- Isn't SHUHUA goofy at times?
- She is.

751
00:25:12,035 --> 00:25:13,334
I heard you ran away from home,

752
00:25:13,335 --> 00:25:14,605
leaving just a piece of tissue behind.

753
00:25:14,965 --> 00:25:17,274
- I didn't run away from home.
- What?

754
00:25:17,275 --> 00:25:19,274
- But she did leave home.
- I did leave home.

755
00:25:19,275 --> 00:25:20,544
- Just after we debuted, - Yes?

756
00:25:20,545 --> 00:25:22,644
we lived in different houses.

757
00:25:22,645 --> 00:25:24,745
I lived with SHUHUA back then.

758
00:25:24,875 --> 00:25:28,145
It's usually noisy in the mornings, but it was quiet that day.

759
00:25:28,345 --> 00:25:30,854
When I left my room, I saw a piece of tissue...

760
00:25:30,855 --> 00:25:32,484
- on SHUHUA's room door.
- A tissue?

761
00:25:32,485 --> 00:25:34,384
Yes, she had stuck a tissue on the door.

762
00:25:34,385 --> 00:25:36,855
The tissue said, "SHUHUA is traveling."

763
00:25:37,055 --> 00:25:39,995
When I opened the door, nobody was in the room.

764
00:25:40,765 --> 00:25:42,794
She disappeared out of nowhere,

765
00:25:42,795 --> 00:25:44,764
so I gave her a call, and she was on a trip.

766
00:25:44,765 --> 00:25:46,464
- Where did you go?
- Where did you go, SHUHUA?

767
00:25:46,465 --> 00:25:50,234
I just took a bus without a specific destination.

768
00:25:50,235 --> 00:25:51,874
- Really?
- Just anywhere?

769
00:25:51,875 --> 00:25:54,604
- Why?
- Why? Were you upset?

770
00:25:54,605 --> 00:25:55,774
I wasn't upset.

771
00:25:55,775 --> 00:25:56,874
- For no reason?
- No.

772
00:25:56,875 --> 00:25:58,875
I simply wanted to leave.

773
00:25:58,945 --> 00:26:00,045
When did you return?

774
00:26:00,315 --> 00:26:01,744
- When?
- In the evening?

775
00:26:01,745 --> 00:26:03,414
No, it was 5pm or 6pm.

776
00:26:03,415 --> 00:26:05,354
- The same day?
- That's just an outing.

777
00:26:05,355 --> 00:26:07,384
- Come on. That wasn't a trip.
- How short.

778
00:26:07,385 --> 00:26:08,954
- That's an outing.
- It's a picnic.

779
00:26:08,955 --> 00:26:10,654
But SHUHUA barely goes out.

780
00:26:10,655 --> 00:26:13,695
- To me, it was...
- She doesn't even like the sun.

781
00:26:13,895 --> 00:26:15,294
You could've just told MIYEON.

782
00:26:15,295 --> 00:26:16,534
Why did you leave it on a tissue?

783
00:26:16,535 --> 00:26:18,234
- It sounds like a travel show.
- MIYEON was sleeping.

784
00:26:18,235 --> 00:26:20,304
- Since she was sleeping.
- Since she was sleeping?

785
00:26:20,305 --> 00:26:22,004
You didn't want her to get worried?

786
00:26:22,005 --> 00:26:24,374
- She was being considerate.
- Gosh, how nice.

787
00:26:24,375 --> 00:26:26,874
Soo Geun ran away from home when he was in middle school,

788
00:26:26,875 --> 00:26:28,374
and his parents didn't know for three days.

789
00:26:28,375 --> 00:26:29,404
- Really?
- Yes.

790
00:26:29,405 --> 00:26:32,175
It wasn't three days. I returned after a week,

791
00:26:32,815 --> 00:26:34,215
and my dad said, "Aren't you going to eat?"

792
00:26:34,885 --> 00:26:35,885
- He didn't know.
- I knew it.

793
00:26:35,886 --> 00:26:39,284
So I realized that my parents weren't that interested.

794
00:26:39,285 --> 00:26:40,684
I hadn't been eating for six days,

795
00:26:40,685 --> 00:26:42,054
- Gosh.
- and we met on the seventh day,

796
00:26:42,055 --> 00:26:43,394
- Unbelievable.
- and he asked if I would eat.

797
00:26:43,395 --> 00:26:45,494
- So I said, "No, I'm not eating."
- Gosh.

798
00:26:45,495 --> 00:26:48,465
- A long time ago, Soo Geun was...
- That's amazing.

799
00:26:48,865 --> 00:26:52,934
going to run away to Seoul from Yangpyeong...

800
00:26:52,935 --> 00:26:54,734
- with his friend.
- Yes.

801
00:26:54,735 --> 00:26:57,374
But when he was leaving to meet him,

802
00:26:57,375 --> 00:26:58,774
- he didn't have any bus money, - That's right.

803
00:26:58,775 --> 00:26:59,874
- I ran away.
- so...

804
00:26:59,875 --> 00:27:01,374
- he couldn't run away...
- Actually...

805
00:27:01,375 --> 00:27:03,174
- and returned home.
- To be honest,

806
00:27:03,175 --> 00:27:05,074
- back in 1980, - That happens.

807
00:27:05,075 --> 00:27:07,244
I almost immigrated to the US.

808
00:27:07,245 --> 00:27:09,045
- Really?
- During the Team Spirit exercise,

809
00:27:09,985 --> 00:27:11,914
there was this American that I knew and he asked me to come.

810
00:27:11,915 --> 00:27:14,584
- Did you almost follow?
- If only I had gotten on that tank.

811
00:27:14,585 --> 00:27:17,224
- A tank?
- I could have become an ARMY.

812
00:27:17,225 --> 00:27:19,324
- An ARMY?
- ARMY.

813
00:27:19,325 --> 00:27:20,394
I could have had lots of C-rations...

814
00:27:20,395 --> 00:27:21,794
- and chocolate.
- The U.S. military.

815
00:27:21,795 --> 00:27:22,965
You don't know what that is, do you?

816
00:27:23,165 --> 00:27:24,564
We have those memories.

817
00:27:24,565 --> 00:27:26,764
(Soo Geun's Back in the Days, Runaway Episode)

818
00:27:26,765 --> 00:27:28,364
- Next question.
- That was funny.

819
00:27:28,365 --> 00:27:31,075
We will look into the transfer students' recent activities.

820
00:27:31,375 --> 00:27:33,004
They wrote here,

821
00:27:33,005 --> 00:27:34,805
"Gimme Dat Love."

822
00:27:34,905 --> 00:27:37,144
- "Gimme Dat Love."
- "Gimme Dat Love."

823
00:27:37,145 --> 00:27:40,014
Is that the title of your new song?

824
00:27:40,015 --> 00:27:41,085
- That's right.
- That's right.

825
00:27:42,815 --> 00:27:46,825
(The title song of their 9th mini album, "We made")

826
00:27:47,055 --> 00:27:48,655
- This song is...
- Yes.

827
00:27:48,985 --> 00:27:50,694
- Well, it's the summertime, - Yes.

828
00:27:50,695 --> 00:27:52,524
and during the summer,

829
00:27:52,525 --> 00:27:54,895
we used to release refreshing songs...

830
00:27:55,095 --> 00:27:56,964
- like "Klaxon."
- Yes.

831
00:27:56,965 --> 00:27:59,394
But this time, we prepared a hotter song...

832
00:27:59,395 --> 00:28:03,434
- so that you can beat the heat.
- Gosh.

833
00:28:03,435 --> 00:28:05,875
It's about real love.

834
00:28:06,035 --> 00:28:07,604
- Totally about love?
- Yes.

835
00:28:07,605 --> 00:28:10,914
Did you not have any complaints about line distribution this time?

836
00:28:10,915 --> 00:28:11,915
- Vocal part distribution.
- Between you guys.

837
00:28:11,916 --> 00:28:14,014
- Last time, MIYEON said that...
- You guys had...

838
00:28:14,015 --> 00:28:15,945
- it was unexpected.
- lots of complaints last time.

839
00:28:16,815 --> 00:28:21,555
(Honestly, I'm not happy with SOYEON's line distribution.)

840
00:28:21,985 --> 00:28:23,194
(Our Thai member!)

841
00:28:23,195 --> 00:28:25,824
(The two foreign members were especially dissatisfied.)

842
00:28:25,825 --> 00:28:27,994
(Speechless)

843
00:28:27,995 --> 00:28:30,865
(She has the most lines!)

844
00:28:31,695 --> 00:28:34,705
(The team is facing a crisis.)

845
00:28:34,805 --> 00:28:36,164
This can be a sensitive topic.

846
00:28:36,165 --> 00:28:37,705
- Well...
- The line distribution...

847
00:28:38,105 --> 00:28:39,574
This time, when we were making the title song,

848
00:28:39,575 --> 00:28:41,474
I contacted SOYEON for the first time.

849
00:28:41,475 --> 00:28:43,144
- Did she?
- Yes, she contacted me.

850
00:28:43,145 --> 00:28:44,145
- What did she say?
- I mean...

851
00:28:44,645 --> 00:28:46,244
My part was so little.

852
00:28:46,245 --> 00:28:48,384
- So...
- What?

853
00:28:48,385 --> 00:28:49,414
- What?
- So...

854
00:28:49,415 --> 00:28:51,084
- Then you should call her.
- No, it's...

855
00:28:51,085 --> 00:28:52,085
- Yes.
- It's true.

856
00:28:52,086 --> 00:28:53,584
It really was my first time contacting her for that.

857
00:28:53,585 --> 00:28:55,624
- What did you say?
- I thought about it all night.

858
00:28:55,625 --> 00:28:58,255
- Did you?
- I listened to the song, and...

859
00:28:58,655 --> 00:29:00,194
I thought to myself, "I'm a main vocalist."

860
00:29:00,195 --> 00:29:02,094
"This just doesn't feel right."

861
00:29:02,095 --> 00:29:04,464
So I wrote it and deleted it over and over again.

862
00:29:04,465 --> 00:29:05,964
I sent her a really long message.

863
00:29:05,965 --> 00:29:07,765
- Yes, it was really long.
- So...

864
00:29:07,965 --> 00:29:10,674
I asked her if I could get a few more lines,

865
00:29:10,675 --> 00:29:13,644
so she gave me a bit of hers.

866
00:29:13,645 --> 00:29:15,104
- Really?
- She's nice.

867
00:29:15,105 --> 00:29:16,744
- Really? I didn't know that.
- Instead of the others?

868
00:29:16,745 --> 00:29:20,344
There was a rap-like part in the middle of the song.

869
00:29:20,345 --> 00:29:23,144
It used to be a rap line when I sang it,

870
00:29:23,145 --> 00:29:25,854
but I switched it to a melody...

871
00:29:25,855 --> 00:29:27,324
and let her sing.

872
00:29:27,325 --> 00:29:28,655
(She gave her part to MIYEON by changing it into a vocal line.)

873
00:29:28,755 --> 00:29:31,195
- Last time, MINNIE said that...
- That's so nice.

874
00:29:31,455 --> 00:29:33,664
she didn't have many lines,

875
00:29:33,665 --> 00:29:35,325
so she was upset. Are you okay this time?

876
00:29:35,665 --> 00:29:36,895
It's really great.

877
00:29:37,295 --> 00:29:39,464
- Is it true?
- I didn't say anything this time.

878
00:29:39,465 --> 00:29:40,534
- You didn't?
- You didn't?

879
00:29:40,535 --> 00:29:41,864
- Just me.
- Because...

880
00:29:41,865 --> 00:29:45,274
Because this time, I got to sing the intro again.

881
00:29:45,275 --> 00:29:48,345
- Did you?
- The intro is really important.

882
00:29:49,405 --> 00:29:51,274
(The vocal tone is so unique, so it's even more memorable.)

883
00:29:51,275 --> 00:29:53,144
(MINNIE's intro is a true work of art.)

884
00:29:53,145 --> 00:29:55,015
(The relaxed low voice is so charming.)

885
00:29:55,145 --> 00:29:56,784
- The intro is really important.
- It is.

886
00:29:56,785 --> 00:29:58,514
- It's been such a long time.
- It captivates.

887
00:29:58,515 --> 00:30:00,254
- That's why I didn't say anything.
- So I...

888
00:30:00,255 --> 00:30:02,124
- Were you okay, - SHUHUA.

889
00:30:02,125 --> 00:30:03,724
- YUQI and SHUHUA?
- Are you okay?

890
00:30:03,725 --> 00:30:05,354
- I'm totally satisfied.
- SHUHUA is satisfied?

891
00:30:05,355 --> 00:30:07,164
- What about YUQI? Be honest.
- Oh, yes.

892
00:30:07,165 --> 00:30:09,324
- Wait.
- What? YUQI has something to say.

893
00:30:09,325 --> 00:30:10,694
- YUQI has something to say.
- No, I don't.

894
00:30:10,695 --> 00:30:11,695
- YUQI...
- No.

895
00:30:11,696 --> 00:30:13,765
I think YUQI doesn't like having many lines.

896
00:30:14,005 --> 00:30:15,005
- Right?
- No...

897
00:30:15,006 --> 00:30:16,264
She has to go to the bank.

898
00:30:16,265 --> 00:30:17,904
She can't practice.

899
00:30:17,905 --> 00:30:19,074
- She wants to shorten the time.
- She's busy.

900
00:30:19,075 --> 00:30:20,075
It's right next door.

901
00:30:20,076 --> 00:30:21,104
- She has to go.
- Because...

902
00:30:21,105 --> 00:30:23,574
The bank is cool during the summer.

903
00:30:23,575 --> 00:30:25,114
Banks are the best place to be during the summer.

904
00:30:25,115 --> 00:30:27,344
- But YUQI...
- That's right.

905
00:30:27,345 --> 00:30:30,285
- Yes?
- Last time, YUQI...

906
00:30:30,515 --> 00:30:32,684
- She had many things to say...
- Yes, she did.

907
00:30:32,685 --> 00:30:34,484
- about her lines.
- That's right.

908
00:30:34,485 --> 00:30:35,824
You didn't contact me this time.

909
00:30:35,825 --> 00:30:37,494
- Are you okay this time around?
- Why not? Were you satisfied?

910
00:30:37,495 --> 00:30:39,725
I'm really okay with it all, because...

911
00:30:40,165 --> 00:30:41,794
I realized this.

912
00:30:41,795 --> 00:30:44,264
Rather than the number of lines,

913
00:30:44,265 --> 00:30:45,394
bringing that part to life...

914
00:30:45,395 --> 00:30:47,504
and making it a killing part is up to me.

915
00:30:47,505 --> 00:30:48,505
- That's it.
- Gosh.

916
00:30:48,506 --> 00:30:50,074
And because...

917
00:30:50,075 --> 00:30:53,474
The reason YUQI is this comfortable is because...

918
00:30:53,475 --> 00:30:56,575
she became the first foreign idol member...

919
00:30:57,015 --> 00:30:59,644
to become a full member of the Korea Music Copyright Association.

920
00:30:59,645 --> 00:31:01,844
- Really?
- Shouldn't Sang Min say it?

921
00:31:01,845 --> 00:31:03,414
- It's true.
- She did.

922
00:31:03,415 --> 00:31:06,755
- She's the first foreigner.
- That's why she's laid back.

923
00:31:07,025 --> 00:31:08,624
Full members have a lot of benefits.

924
00:31:08,625 --> 00:31:10,594
That's why I'm okay here.

925
00:31:10,595 --> 00:31:11,754
No wonder.

926
00:31:11,755 --> 00:31:14,324
The important thing is, there's a new president now,

927
00:31:14,325 --> 00:31:15,925
- so the pension has changed...
- What?

928
00:31:16,225 --> 00:31:18,164
from 700 dollars to 1,000 dollars monthly.

929
00:31:18,165 --> 00:31:19,664
- What?
- I mean, from 600 to 1,000 monthly.

930
00:31:19,665 --> 00:31:22,664
Sang Min, I'm sorry, but do you have a role there?

931
00:31:22,665 --> 00:31:25,074
- He must be the president.
- Is Sang Min a full member?

932
00:31:25,075 --> 00:31:27,074
I have a question. If you are a full member,

933
00:31:27,075 --> 00:31:29,574
I heard that you got gifts...

934
00:31:29,575 --> 00:31:30,914
during the holidays.

935
00:31:30,915 --> 00:31:32,874
- They send gifts.
- They do.

936
00:31:32,875 --> 00:31:35,144
- I got fish once, - Yes.

937
00:31:35,145 --> 00:31:36,244
- What?
- and even meat.

938
00:31:36,245 --> 00:31:37,254
- Really?
- What?

939
00:31:37,255 --> 00:31:39,355
- And...
- What? I only got seaweed.

940
00:31:39,485 --> 00:31:42,285
- You only got seaweed?
- The ex-president liked seaweed.

941
00:31:43,325 --> 00:31:44,694
It must have been from the new president.

942
00:31:44,695 --> 00:31:46,694
- Is that so?
- The president has changed.

943
00:31:46,695 --> 00:31:48,164
The president changed?

944
00:31:48,165 --> 00:31:49,165
- Yes.
- That's why.

945
00:31:49,166 --> 00:31:51,764
- No wonder.
- I got it this time.

946
00:31:51,765 --> 00:31:53,504
- Really?
- Is he from a different place?

947
00:31:53,505 --> 00:31:54,505
(A reliable source of information)

948
00:31:54,506 --> 00:31:55,634
- He must be from elsewhere.
- No way.

949
00:31:55,635 --> 00:31:58,334
- But if YUQI got the gifts, - Gosh.

950
00:31:58,335 --> 00:32:00,644
then SOYEON should get the same gifts.

951
00:32:00,645 --> 00:32:02,274
- She should...
- I didn't...

952
00:32:02,275 --> 00:32:03,945
If you don't attend the regular meeting three times,

953
00:32:04,415 --> 00:32:05,544
- Do you get kicked out?
- you get removed.

954
00:32:05,545 --> 00:32:06,574
You need to attend them.

955
00:32:06,575 --> 00:32:08,244
- I...
- Maybe you got kicked out.

956
00:32:08,245 --> 00:32:09,984
- You must have gotten kicked out.
- I think you got kicked out.

